pros:
- Good pay/package with base, bonus and other perks;
- Team/Project dependent but usually you can find and build great "work friends" relationships;
- A company that takes care of its employees; unless you do something stupid there's a low chance you'll get fired;
- Good work/life balance - there is no pressure to deliver.

cons:
- It's very political, it matters more who and how you talk to people than your actual professional skills and being able to deliver;
- Collaboration mindset misunderstood/taken to extreme. Everybody must agree and hold hands even if they don't understand the topic or dedicate the time needed to understand it.
- Wrong people taking the decisions or right people using wrong data taking the decisions. The result is the same.
